data.content:
Here are the three breaking changes affecting your code in EF Core 10, with fixes:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual expression-tree building **won't compile** because the parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`.

**Fix** — replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` gymnastics needed.

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified

`ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column. EF 10 appends a number to disambiguate, **breaking existing schemas**. Nested types also change: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (full path) instead of `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** — pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin to the old (short) name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (contains potentially-redacted SQL for logging).

**Fix:**

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (redacted constants)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update all other interface methods (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) similarly.
